1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 23=
(Let's Keep A Secret Together)

16
00:01:52,910 --> 00:01:53,340
Liu Yuan.

17
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:55,940
You told me the questions
were authentic.

18
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:57,960
Why didn't I get any question right?
Explain.

19
00:01:58,580 --> 00:01:59,110
Pal.

20
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,390
You got it wrong.

21
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:01,340
How could I

22
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:02,270
get the real questions?

23
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:04,420
What I sold you are

24
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:06,220
the mock questions I compiled
from previous

25
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,990
years' advanced mathematics exams.

26
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:10,180
I spent 500 yuan
to buy your mock questions?

27
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:11,800
Which one of us is crazy?

28
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:12,620
Pal.

29
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:14,390
Speak with evidence.

30
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,950
Don't make unfounded accusations.

31
00:02:16,790 --> 00:02:17,580
Even so,

32
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:19,460
if I sold the real questions,

33
00:02:19,790 --> 00:02:20,950
it would be cheating.

34
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:22,700
You should report me
to the dean's office

35
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:24,580
instead of buying my exam questions.

36
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:28,460
Forget it.

37
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,270
You old fraud.

38
00:02:29,270 --> 00:02:29,700
Come down!

39
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:30,390
Forget it.

40
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:31,860
Don't argue with him.

41
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:32,760
Forget it. Let's go.

42
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:33,620
Come down!

43
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:34,110
Don't.

44
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:35,620
Calm down.

45
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:36,180
You old fraud!

46
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:36,620
Go.

47
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:37,620
Enough.

48
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:40,950
(Calm)

49
00:02:40,950 --> 00:02:42,070
Why did you stop me just now?

50
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,790
I should have beaten him black and blue

51
00:02:43,790 --> 00:02:44,900
and given him a lesson.

52
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:46,550
Just save your energy.

53
00:02:46,790 --> 00:02:47,350
You should

54
00:02:47,350 --> 00:02:48,830
take this as a lesson.

55
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:49,900
Just don't do it again.

56
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:50,900
No.

57
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,080
I can't swallow this.

58
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,920
Come back.

59
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:55,700
Think about it.

60
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,660
If you beat him up,

61
00:02:56,660 --> 00:02:58,180
not only you can't get your money back,

62
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,720
but you also pay
for his medical expenses.

63
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,540
People like him

64
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:01,620
will blackmail you.

65
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:02,700
You'll suffer.

66
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:04,350
Jeez.

67
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:06,620
Jing's right.

68
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:07,580
You

69
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:09,240
should endure it
and let things calm down.

70
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:10,230
I understand.

71
00:03:11,670 --> 00:03:12,420
Endure it?

72
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,440
The more I think about it,
the angrier I get.

73
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,950
Anger will hurt your liver, young man.

74
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:17,620
No.

75
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:18,830
It's easy for you to say.

76
00:03:19,670 --> 00:03:20,830
It's 500 yuan.

77
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:22,020
I can buy so many eggs.

78
00:03:24,670 --> 00:03:25,140
No.

79
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,560
I want to beat him!

80
00:03:29,990 --> 00:03:30,860
Don't stop me!

81
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:32,420
I'm going to beat him!

82
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:34,900
- Calm down!
- Put me down!

83
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,230
(The first semester of freshman year)

84
00:03:38,670 --> 00:03:39,900
(ends just like that.)

85
00:03:41,420 --> 00:03:42,420
(Our Top Student)

86
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:44,300
(got first place again as she wished.)

87
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,180
(Wu'an University Final Exam Transcript)

88
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:48,860
(Zhou Ye paid 500 yuan)

89
00:03:48,860 --> 00:03:50,520
(and still failed the exam.)

90
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,900
(Wu'an University Final Exam Transcript)

91
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,110
(As for Huang Lu and Qiu Li...)

92
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:54,700
(One scored 56.)

93
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,140
(One scored 59.)

94
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:57,110
(Obviously,)

95
00:03:57,740 --> 00:03:58,950
(Qiu Li who scored 59)

96
00:03:58,950 --> 00:04:00,900
(is angrier than Huang Lu.)

97
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,440
How come you scored more than me?

98
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,740
Aren't I still one mark short?

99
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:10,550
Hello, Sir.

100
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:12,020
Could you help me check

101
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:14,420
and see if you miscalculated?

102
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:18,380
(As for me,)

103
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:19,990
(not that bad.)

104
00:04:20,470 --> 00:04:21,500
(My score is 76.)

105
00:04:22,030 --> 00:04:23,990
(There's still
a lot of room for improvement.)

106
00:04:27,829 --> 00:04:28,380
(Transcript)

107
00:04:28,380 --> 00:04:30,160
(But what I didn't expect
is that Jing Xichi)

108
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,230
(is no longer
at the bottom of the class)

109
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,800
(like he did in senior middle school)

110
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:35,680
(and got full marks
in Advanced Mathematics.)

111
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,060
(But no matter how we did in the exam,)

112
00:04:38,910 --> 00:04:41,910
(these are already
preludes in the river of time.)

113
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:43,790
(As for)

114
00:04:44,180 --> 00:04:45,710
(those unfinished stories,)

115
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,990
(let's wait until next semester.)

116
00:04:58,338 --> 00:05:00,420
(Ultrasound Diagnostic Report)

117
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:01,150
Enough.

118
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,550
Stop looking at it.

119
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:04,940
We'll only know

120
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,080
if it's benign or malignant
after the biopsy.

121
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:08,350
What's a biopsy?

122
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:10,860
A biopsy means cutting it out

123
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:12,140
for an examination.

124
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,080
Hurry and do it then.

125
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,030
What are you doing here?

126
00:05:14,030 --> 00:05:15,990
Do you think it's as easy
as cutting vegetables?

127
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,420
You'll make an appointment.

128
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:18,820
So have you made an appointment?

129
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,020
Yes.

130
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,380
Take it easy.

131
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:22,420
I'm a doctor.

132
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:23,590
I know what to do.

133
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,030
You make it sound so simple.

134
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:26,470
How could I not be nervous?

135
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:28,110
Swallow it.

136
00:05:29,990 --> 00:05:31,060
Don't let Huan'er know.

137
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:32,500
She will be back soon.

138
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:33,740
Hurry and put it away.

139
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:35,940
We have a table of vegetables to pick.

140
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:37,110
Hurry!

141
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:37,550
Mom.

142
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:38,300
Put it away.

143
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,590
I'm back!

144
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,420
Coming!

145
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,230
My daughter is back.

146
00:05:43,230 --> 00:05:44,060
Mom!

147
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:46,420
Darling, you're back.

148
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:47,670
Chubby bunny.

149
00:05:47,670 --> 00:05:48,100
Let me see

150
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,260
- if you gained weight.
- Your dad had been waiting.

151
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:51,060
One, two, three.

152
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,350
She's like a piglet.

153
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:52,990
Put her down.

154
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,260
You're old now. Watch your waist!

155
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:54,670
Not bad.

156
00:05:54,670 --> 00:05:55,500
You gained weight.

157
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:56,620
Did I gain weight?

158
00:05:56,620 --> 00:05:57,110
No.

159
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:57,820
Hurry. Sit.

160
00:05:58,110 --> 00:05:58,820
I almost forgot...

161
00:05:58,990 --> 00:05:59,380
Dad, Mom.

162
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:00,990
I have a surprise for you.

163
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:03,030
You brought us gifts?

164
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:03,380
Yes.

165
00:06:03,380 --> 00:06:04,470
Did you buy our gifts

166
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:05,590
with our money?

167
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:06,420
- Jeez.
- Here.

168
00:06:06,420 --> 00:06:07,790
I prepared it myself.

169
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:08,550
Really?

170
00:06:08,710 --> 00:06:09,670
Here, let me see.

171
00:06:10,230 --> 00:06:10,740
Gosh.

172
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:11,670
Look at this.

173
00:06:11,710 --> 00:06:13,080
Look who she took after.

174
00:06:16,590 --> 00:06:17,300
Oh no.

175
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,620
No, Chen Huan'er.

176
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:19,710
What are you doing?

177
00:06:19,860 --> 00:06:21,380
You have to tighten these bottles

178
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:23,110
before putting them in.

179
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:24,110
You just put

180
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:24,740
everything in.

181
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:25,820
Now I know.

182
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,060
It's my fault for not nurturing

183
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,300
your life skills well.

184
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:28,710
Enough.

185
00:06:28,710 --> 00:06:29,860
What will you do without me?

186
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:30,980
I knitted the scarves myself.

187
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:31,790
Stop nagging.

188
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:32,110
Enough.

189
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,500
It's a token of her sincerity.

190
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:34,710
I knitted

191
00:06:34,710 --> 00:06:35,860
this red one for you.

192
00:06:36,670 --> 00:06:38,180
The blue one is for Dad.

193
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:38,860
Sure.

194
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:40,990
There are only a few more stitches left.

195
00:06:40,990 --> 00:06:42,040
I'll hurry up these days.

196
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,620
It's fragrant.

197
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:43,140
How nice.

198
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:44,790
Do you like it, Mom?

199
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:46,260
This color

200
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:46,820
is not bad.

201
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:49,740
The stitching

202
00:06:49,820 --> 00:06:51,040
is not bad either.

203
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,470
You're talented.

204
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:54,180
My classmate taught me.

205
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:54,590
Good.

206
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:55,350
Chen.

207
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,670
Hurry and wash it for me.

208
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:58,420
I don't need to buy a scarf this year.

209
00:06:58,910 --> 00:06:59,420
Okay.

210
00:06:59,420 --> 00:06:59,990
Wash it clean.

211
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:00,710
Do you like it?

212
00:07:00,790 --> 00:07:01,350
Okay.

213
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:02,910
My daughter did a good job.

214
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:03,740
Come and sit down.

215
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:04,860
I have something for you.

216
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,030
How comfortable.

217
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:09,500
Mom.

218
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:11,860
I want beef with celery today.

219
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,940
Your favorite
stir-fried beef with celery.

220
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:14,710
Here.

221
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:16,740
Sign this.

222
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,140
(Insurance Contract)
Insurance?

223
00:07:18,620 --> 00:07:20,230
Why did you suddenly buy insurance?

224
00:07:21,470 --> 00:07:22,550
I thought it was suitable

225
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,670
and bought it for you.

226
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,790
You'll be insured
and won't suffer any loss.

227
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,230
Besides,

228
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,030
you're a grown-up girl.

229
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:31,470
Huan'er.

230
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:32,860
You've grown up.

231
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:34,800
You need to learn
to take care of yourself.

232
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:36,420
I can't

233
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:37,470
stay by your side forever.

234
00:07:37,550 --> 00:07:38,110
No.

235
00:07:38,590 --> 00:07:39,820
I want to be with you forever.

236
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:40,820
I don't care.

237
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:42,710
Enough.

238
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,440
Hurry and put those things away.

239
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:45,110
Later,

240
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:46,590
Song Cong, Jing and their families

241
00:07:46,590 --> 00:07:47,660
will be here for a meal.

242
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:48,300
Look at you.

243
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,790
When will they be here?

244
00:07:49,790 --> 00:07:51,030
Soon.

245
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:52,620
I don't care. Put it away yourself.

246
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:57,420
Mom, I'll put it in the toilet first.

247
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:21,590
How dare you come back?

248
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,440
Why did you change your major?

249
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:38,110
Many people try very hard to get into

250
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,480
the law program at University
of Political Science and Law.

251
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:41,830
Look at you!

252
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,990
You changed to some literature?

253
00:08:45,070 --> 00:08:45,830
I'm just trying

254
00:08:45,830 --> 00:08:46,840
to do what I want.

255
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,320
You're using your family's money

256
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:51,470
to do what you want.

257
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,190
What an easy life.

258
00:08:58,620 --> 00:09:00,660
You don't have
to pressure me with money.

259
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:02,580
I know that parents have no obligation

260
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:03,960
to support their adult children.

261
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,820
I'll find a way to pay
for my future tuition.

262
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:06,880
You don't have to worry.

263
00:09:07,830 --> 00:09:09,230
I'm an adult now.

264
00:09:09,830 --> 00:09:11,540
You're no longer my guardian.

265
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:15,320
You've grown capable
since going to university.

266
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:16,590
Sure.

267
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:18,470
Since you're talking to me
about the law,

268
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:19,500
let me tell you

269
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:22,350
that adult children
have a lifetime obligation

270
00:09:22,350 --> 00:09:23,540
to support their parents.

271
00:09:25,110 --> 00:09:26,070
As long as I live,

272
00:09:26,780 --> 00:09:28,070
you'll always be my daughter.

273
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:29,990
You can never repay

274
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:31,950
what you owe me.

275
00:09:32,590 --> 00:09:33,350
Okay.

276
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:35,990
Go ahead and sue me, Ms. Qi.

277
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,430
I'll repay you whatever amount
the court sentences me.

278
00:09:38,710 --> 00:09:39,110
By then,

279
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:40,190
we'll be completely even.

280
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:55,310
Be careful. Don't burn yourself.

281
00:09:55,310 --> 00:09:55,830
Here.

282
00:09:55,830 --> 00:09:56,620
Be careful.

283
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,500
Be careful, Mom.

284
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:58,900
It's hot, Mom.

285
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,590
Amazing. You cooked so much.

286
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:01,500
Here.

287
00:10:01,590 --> 00:10:02,140
Here.

288
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:03,710
Here, you can start.

289
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:04,300
You can do it.

290
